```json
// .vscode/settings.json
{
  "editor.formatOnSave": true,
  "editor.defaultFormatter": "charliermarsh.ruff",
  "python.analysis.typeCheckingMode": "basic",
  "[python]": { "editor.codeActionsOnSave": { "source.organizeImports": "explicit" } }
}
```

Committing `.vscode/settings.json` means every contributor (and future-you on a new machine) gets identical formatting and type-checking with zero setup. Format-on-save ends all whitespace/style diffs; `basic` type checking catches the `None`-attribute and wrong-argument bugs that otherwise surface only at runtime.
